  "prompt": "What is the medical condition MDS?",
  "response": "MDS stands for Myelodysplastic Syndromes, which are a group of blood and bone marrow disorders. In MDS, the bone marrow fails to produce enough healthy blood cells, leading to low blood cell counts. Key characteristics include:\n\n1. Symptoms:\n- Fatigue\n- Frequent infections\n- Easy bruising or bleeding\n- Shortness of breath\n\n2. Types:\n- Several subtypes based on specific blood cell abnormalities\n- Classified by genetic changes and percentage of abnormal cells\n\n3. Causes:\n- Can be primary (unknown origin)\n- Secondary (caused by chemotherapy, radiation, or chemical exposure)\n- Some genetic factors\n\n4. Risk factors:\n- Age (more common in older adults)\n- Previous cancer treatments\n- Exposure to certain chemicals\n- Smoking\n\n5. Potential complications:\n- Increased risk of developing acute myeloid leukemia (AML)\n- Severe anemia\n- Increased infection risk\n\n6. Treatment options:\n- Supportive care\n- Blood transfusions\n- Medications\n- Chemotherapy\n- Stem cell transplant (in some cases)\n\nMDS is a serious condition that requires medical management and ongoing monitoring by healthcare professionals.",
